the essential characteristics of science are:
(1) It is guided by natural law;
(2) It has to be explanatory by reference to nature law;
(3) It is testable against the empirical world;
(4) Its conclusions are tentative, i.e. are not necessarily the final word; and
(5) Its is falsifiable. (Ruse and other science witnesses).<p><a href="http://www.talkorigins.org/faqs/mclean-v-arkansas.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.talkorigins.org/faqs/mclean-v-arkansas.html</a>
